
## 🔹 **4. PHP Constants**

Constants are fixed values
Cannot be changed once created
Defined using `define()`
No `$` symbol used


### Example

<?php
define("SITE_NAME", "My Website");

echo SITE_NAME;
?>

## PHP Concatenation

Used to join strings
Operator used → `.`

### Example

<?php
$name = "Sdr";
echo "Hello " . $name;
?>

Summary 
* Scope → Global, Local, Static
* Data Types → String, Integer, Float, Boolean, Array, Null
* Arrays → Indexed & Associative
* Constants → Fixed values using `define()`
* Concatenation → Join strings using `.`
